1 of l oss. Upon a judgment rendered to either party, costs and
2 attorney fees shall be allowable to the prevailing party. For
3 purposes of this section, the prevailing party is the insurer in
4 those cases where judgment does not exceed written offer of
5 settlement. In all other judgments the insured shall be the
6 prevailing party. If the insured is the prevailing party, the court
7 in rendering judgment shall add interest on the verdict at the rate
8 of fifteen percent (15%) per year from the date the loss was payable
9 pursuant to the provisions of the contract to the date of the
10 verdict. This provision shall not apply to uninsured motorist
11 coverage or property insurance as defined in Section 704 of Title 36
12 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
